The Nigerian Youth and Diaspora Forum For Bola Ahmed Tinubu (NYD4BAT) during its inaguration on April 27, 2022 at the Lagos Chambers of Commerce and Industry (LCCI) Hall, Alausa-Ikeja will unveil an e-campaign in support of the presidential aspiration of the former Lagos State governor. Dr Ajibola Abayomi, the Director of Media and Publicity for the group in statement said “our unconditional support for the national leader of the All Progressive Congress, (APC) is total and voluntary. We are bringing into fore a knowledge driven campaign based on the huge contributions of the Jagaban to the Nigerian democracy coupled with his untiring efforts as a nation and youths builder over the years. “We believe Asiwaju is well prepared for the Nigerian presidency unlike others who are either waiting to be annointed or rehearsing gatecrashing strategies to emerge like accidental leaders. That we don’t want”. Both Nigerian based at home and abroad, and a political group named Women for Asiwaju are expected at the event. Guest speakers are former Speaker Lagos State House of Assembly, Hon Jokotola Pelumi; Hon Lanre Odubote, a former House Reps member and an adviser to the Speaker House of Reps, Hon Femi Gbajabiamila; Spokesman of the Lagos State APC, Hon Seye Oladejo, Romania based Executive Director Nigerian Diaspora Project 4040, Adeniyi Sanusi who doubles as NYD4BAT Disapora Chairman and others The NYD4BAT in Nigeria is lead by Tito Philips, Jnr the CEO of MADPhilips Development Company. Apart from unveiling the e-campaign strategies, he ould present a publication containing a 70-point agenda on why Nigerians should support Tinubu as next president during the 2023 elections.